  "runtime": {
    "_notes": [
      "GEMM C = A*B, A is 8x4, B is 4x8, C is 8x8.",
      "Grid = 4 serial CTAs * 16 threads = 64 outputs.",
      "Single-resident-CTA model: only one CTA runs at a time, so the FPGA",
      "controller re-stages CSRs between dispatches. csrX0/1/2 shift by 16",
      "elements per CTA (the per_cta_csr_overrides table); csrX3..5 (k-stride",
      "constants) stay fixed. The kernel reads REGS0 = local_tid (0..15) on",
      "every CTA -- no global thread id needed.",
      "Host pre-shuffles A,B into thread-major layouts:",
      "  A_packed[k*TOTAL + g] = A[g/N][k]",
      "  B_packed[k*TOTAL + g] = B[k][g%N]",
      "where g = cta_id.x * 16 + local_tid (folded into the per-CTA csrX0/1/2).",
      "Thread g's k-th A access lands at: csrX0_for_this_cta + k_stride + REGS0."
    ],
